Package: paletteknife
Title: Create Colour Scales From Continuous Or Categorical Vectors
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
  person(given = "John",
         family = "Hobbs",
         role = c("aut", "cre"),
         email = "johnxhobbs@gmail.com")
Description: This function embeds a few of the most popular colour palettes (ColorBrewer, Viridis, Turbo, and others) 
             and wraps them in a simple helper function which converts values to colour hex strings. The output can 
             be used with the default plot() functions, and the simple autolegend() wrapper for legend().
